FBIS3-37462 "drsov033_a_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-033 Document Type:Daily Report 17 Feb 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Yeltsin, Kohl Discuss Bosnia by Phone LD1602183094 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1707 GMT 16 Feb 94 LD1602183094 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Text] Moscow, 16 Feb (ITAR-TASS) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin has had a telephone conversation with FRG Chancellor Helmut Kohl. Some topical questions of bilateral relations and international policy were discussed. The president's press service reports that both leaders spoke in favor of establishing full-scale cooperation between the G-7 countries and Russia, and its involvement in foreign policy discussions already at the present stage. The main theme of the conversation was an exchange of opinions on the Yugoslav problem. The Russian president stressed that it is necessary to settle the crisis in accordance with UN decisions. Boris Yeltsin and Helmut Kohl agreed to continue the dialogue on the situation in Bosnia in the nearest future and to discuss possibilities for new inititiatives toward a peaceful settlement of the conflict.
